&lt;p&gt;This 13th century Castle is located 45 minutes from Galway city. Once the Estate of Lord Ardilaun and the Guinness family, Ashford opened as a luxury hotel in 1939, making it the oldest castle hotel in Ireland and recently voted the Best Hotel in the World by Virtuoso Awards 2015.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In 2013 Ashford was bought by the Tollman family of the Red Carnation collection, who began a loving restoration project resulting in a &amp;#8220;Palace inside a Castle.&amp;#8221;&lt;br /&gt;
The Castle offers 82 bespoke bedrooms, a 32 seated cinema, multiple dining options, a Library, a Billiard&amp;#8217;s room, a Cigar terrace, a state of the art Spa and beautiful public lounges and 21st Century technology throughout. The Ashford Estate offers an array of activities including Orvis fly fishing to Ireland&amp;#8217;s First school of Falconry, Cruising on Lough Corrib, horseback riding, Archery, Kayaking, Zip wiring and Clay pigeon shooting.&lt;/p&gt;

